{"lemma":"عُداة","slug":"عُداة","root":"ع.د.#","root_slug":"ع-د-_","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-د-_","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"عَدُوّ","root":"عدو","pos":"N","occurrence_count":50},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n28369","n28370"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D9%8F%D8%AF%D8%A7%D8%A9"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"enemy; foe","examples":[{"text":"الْأَخِلَّاءُ يَوْمَئِذٍ بَعْضُهُمْ لِبَعْضٍ عَدُوٌّ إِلَّا الْمُتَّقِينَ","english":"Close friends, that Day, will be enemies to each other, except for the righteous."},{"text":"هُمُ ٱلْعَدُوُّ فَٱحْذَرْهُمْ","english":"They are the enemy, so beware of them."}]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/ʕa.duww/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n28369","headword_ar":"عَدَاهُ","root":"Edw","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh, K,) first pers."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eadawotuhu","text_ar":"عَدَوْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaEoduw","text_ar":"يَعْدُو"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh, Msb,) [inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EadowN","text_ar":"عَدْوٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He passed from it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb, K,) namely, a thing, or an affair, (K,) to another, (Mgh, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and left it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EadaA Eanohu","text_ar":"عَدَا عَنْهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same; (K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tEd~Ah","text_ar":"تعدّاه","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, * K;) and in like manner one says, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ead~ayotuhu","text_ar":"عَدَّيْتُهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taEodiyapN","text_ar":"تَعْدِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Msb;) [but I do not find this elsewhere, and think that correctly one should say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eanohu","text_ar":"عَنْهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ead~ayotu","text_ar":"عَدَّيْتُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; agreeably with what here follows:] the saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eano h`*aA","text_ar":"عَنْ هٰذَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ead~i","text_ar":"عَدِّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Leave thou this,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"turn from it to another;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and is app. from the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ham~aka","text_ar":"هَمَّكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ead~i","text_ar":"عَدِّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_ilaY gayorihi","text_ar":"اـِلَى غَيْرِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Turn thy anxiety to other than him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; the objective complement being altogether left out, so that the verb becomes as though it were intrans.; and there are many instances similar to this in the language: (Har p. 478:) one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ean~iY Alham~a","text_ar":"عَنِّى الهَمَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ead~ayotu","text_ar":"عَدَّيْتُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I turned away from me anxiety:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and [hence] you say to him who has pursued you,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ean~iY A_ilaY gayoriY","text_ar":"عَنِّى اـِلَى غَيْرِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ead~i","text_ar":"عَدِّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Turn thou"},{"kind":"text","text":"the beast upon which thou art riding"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"towards other than me:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eam~aA taraY","text_ar":"عَمَّا تَرَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ead~i","text_ar":"عَدِّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Turn thou"},{"kind":"text","text":"thine eye"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from what thou seest."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) [See an ex. of the first of these verbs in the Ham p. 125.] One says also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EadaAhu AlA^amoru","text_ar":"عَدَاهُ الاَمْرُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tEd~Ahu","text_ar":"تعدّاهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"affair, passed from him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA. [See an ex. in the first paragraph of art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Edm","text_ar":"عدم"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) And the Arabs say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_in~a Aljaraba","text_ar":"اـِنَّ الجَرَبَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"layaEoduw","text_ar":"لَيَعْدُو"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily the mange,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"scab, passes"},{"kind":"text","text":"from him that has it to him that is near to him so that the latter becomes mangy, or scabby. (Msb.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA EadaA fulaAnN A^ano SanaEa","text_ar":"مَا عَدَا فُلَانٌ اَنْ صَنَعَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one did not leave,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, accord. to an explanation of the verb in a similar phrase in Har p. 333,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"did not delay, his doing"},{"kind":"text","text":"such a thing]. (S.) Accord. to Er-Rághib,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEadowu","text_ar":"العَدْوُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"primarily signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Transition;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[whence what here precedes;] or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the going,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"passing, beyond,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the exceeding,"},{"kind":"text","text":"a limit, or the usual limit: and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"incompatibility to coalesce."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-  And [hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EadaAhu","text_ar":"عَدَاهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor. as above, [inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EadowN","text_ar":"عَدْوٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He went,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"passed, beyond it; exceeded it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"transgressed it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA. *) So in the saying"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EadaA Taworahu","text_ar":"عَدَا طَوْرَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He went,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"passed, beyond his proper limit; exceeded it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"transgressed it"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and in like manner,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHaq~a","text_ar":"الحَقَّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tEd~Y","text_ar":"تعدّى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AEtdAhu","text_ar":"اعتداهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He went,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"passed, beyond,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what was true,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"right;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eani AlHaq~i","text_ar":"عَنِ الحَقِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fawoqa AlHaq~i","text_ar":"فَوْقَ الحَقِّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amaA","text_ar":"اَمَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EadaA mano badaA","text_ar":"عَدَا مَنْ بَدَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", a saying in which the vulgar erroneously omit the interrogative"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^","text_ar":"ا"},{"kind":"text","text":", means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Does not he transgress that which is right who begins"},{"kind":"text","text":"by acting injuriously? (TA.) And it is said"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EadaA","text_ar":"عَدَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlqaAriSu faHaraza","text_ar":"القَارِصُ فَحَرَزَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"What was biting to the tongue attained to an excessive degree, so that it became acid:"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning that the affair, or case, became distressing. (S in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qrS","text_ar":"قرص"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EadaA Ealayohi","text_ar":"عَدَا عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EadowN","text_ar":"عَدْوٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EadaA='N","text_ar":"عَدَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Euduw~N","text_ar":"عُدُوٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EudowaAnN","text_ar":"عُدْوَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISd, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EidowaAnN","text_ar":"عِدْوَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISd, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EudowaY","text_ar":"عُدْوَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tEd~Y","text_ar":"تعدّى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AEtdY","text_ar":"اعتدى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, Msb, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He acted wrongfully, unjustly, injuriously,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tyrannically, against him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb, K;) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"transgressed against him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"exceeded the proper limit against him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Msb:) [and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he acted aggressively against him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"agreeably with an explanation of the inf. n. of the last of these verbs in what follows: (see an ex. in a verse cited voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"riyHN","text_ar":"رِيحٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":)] or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he acted with excessive wrongfulness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"against him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AEdY","text_ar":"اعدى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same as the other verbs here mentioned; (K, TA;) whence (TA) one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY manoTiqika","text_ar":"فِى مَنْطِقِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEodayota","text_ar":"اَعْدَيْتَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Thou hast deviated from that which is right in thy speech:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA:) ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlAiEotidaA='u","text_ar":"الاِعْتِدَا=ءُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the exceeding what is right;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and it is sometimes"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the way of aggression;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and sometimes"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the way of requital;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and instances of the usage of its verb in both of these manners occur in the Kur ii. 190: (Er-Rághib, TA:) the first and third of the inf. ns. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EadaA","text_ar":"عَدَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", mentioned above, occur in the Kur vi. 108 accord. to different readings: (S, TA:) and [it is said that]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEudowaAnu","text_ar":"العُدْوَانُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sheer,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unmixed, wrongful"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unjust"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"injurious"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tyrannical conduct:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) or, as some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the worst of"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such conduct,"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlAiEotidaA='","text_ar":"الاِعْتِدَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in strength,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"deed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"state"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"condition."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b4-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EadaA","text_ar":"عَدَا"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealayohi","text_ar":"عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He acted corruptly towards him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b5-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EudiYa Ealayohi","text_ar":"عُدِىَ عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He had his property stolen, and was wronged."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EadaA EalaY AlqumaA$i","text_ar":"عَدَا عَلَى القُمَاشِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EadaA='N","text_ar":"عَدَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[said in the TA to be like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saHaAbN","text_ar":"سَحَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", but in the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EadFA","text_ar":"عَدًا"},{"kind":"text","text":",] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EudowaAnN","text_ar":"عُدْوَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EadawaAnN","text_ar":"عَدَوَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) but in the M written with damm and fet-h [i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EudowaAn","text_ar":"عُدْوَان"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EadowaAn","text_ar":"عَدْوَان"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (TA,) said of a thief,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He stole the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qmA$","text_ar":"قماش"},{"kind":"text","text":"[meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goods,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"utensils and furniture"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (K, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EadaA fiY Zahorihi","text_ar":"عَدَا فِى ظَهْرِهِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He stole what was behind him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Zhr","text_ar":"ظهر"},{"kind":"text","text":":) [or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he acted wrongfully in respect of what was behind him:"},{"kind":"text","text":"for]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"liS~N EaAdiY ZahorK","text_ar":"لِصٌّ عَادِى ظَهْرٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is expl. by the words"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EadaA fiY ZahorK fasaraqahu","text_ar":"عَدَا فِى ظَهْرٍ فَسَرَقَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[so that it app. means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A thief who has acted wrongfully in respect of what was behind one, and stolen it"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (O and K in that art.) ―         -b6-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EadaA Ealayohi","text_ar":"عَدَا عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K, TA,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EadowN","text_ar":"عَدْوٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) signifies also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He leaped upon him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.) ―         -b7-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EadaA","text_ar":"عَدَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EadaA fiY","text_ar":"عَدَا فِى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma$oyihi","text_ar":"مَشْيِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaEoduw","text_ar":"يَعْدُو"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EadowN","text_ar":"عَدْوٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EadFA","text_ar":"عَدًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Euduw~N","text_ar":"عُدُوٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EadawaAnN","text_ar":"عَدَوَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taEodaA='N","text_ar":"تَعْدَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) signifies"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aHoDara","text_ar":"اَحْضَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He ran;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rose in his running"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (S, * K, TA;) said of a man and of a horse: (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he went a pace nearly the same as that termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"harowalapN","text_ar":"هَرْوَلَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not so quick,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which is not so quick,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as that termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaroYN","text_ar":"جَرْىٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he went a pace less quick than"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ad~N","text_ar":"شَدٌّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and more so than"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma$oYN","text_ar":"مَشْىٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sEY","text_ar":"سعى"},{"kind":"text","text":":) or ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he went quickly,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"swiftly;"},{"kind":"text","text":"for]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEadowu","text_ar":"العَدْوُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~uroEapu","text_ar":"السُّرْعَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Mgh:) [or rather"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he ran,"},{"kind":"text","text":"whether"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gently"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"moderately"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vehemently:"},{"kind":"text","text":"that it often signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he ran vehemently"},{"kind":"text","text":"is shown by the prov."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino sulayokK","text_ar":"مِنْ سُلَيْكٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEodaY","text_ar":"اَعْدَى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"More vehement in running than Suleyk,"},{"kind":"text","text":"who is said to have outstripped fleet horses; and by numerous exs.:] and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"E~Y","text_ar":"عّى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EadaA","text_ar":"عَدَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", denoting a quick pace. (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hbS","text_ar":"هبص"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b8-  And [hence, perhaps,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EadaA AlmaA='u","text_ar":"عَدَا المَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaEoduw","text_ar":"يَعْدُو"},{"kind":"text","text":", (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The water ran."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EadaAhu Eani AlA^amori","text_ar":"عَدَاهُ عَنِ الاَمْرِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EadowN","text_ar":"عَدْوٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EudowaAnN","text_ar":"عُدْوَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ed~Ahu","text_ar":"عدّاهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (K;) signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, diverted him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"turned him away,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"back;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K;) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"occupied him so as to divert him;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from the thing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"affair."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eadato EawaAdK","text_ar":"عَدَتْ عَوَادٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, TA. See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAdiyapN","text_ar":"عَادِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EudawaA='u","text_ar":"عُدَوَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and see also the last sentence of the first paragraph of art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ewd","text_ar":"عود"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EadaAniY minohu","text_ar":"عَدَانِى مِنْهُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ar~N","text_ar":"شَرٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"balaganiY","text_ar":"بَلَغَنِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e., app.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Evil,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mischief, reached me from him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA. [See a signi-"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1978},{"kind":"text","text":"fication of 4.])       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eadiytu lahu","text_ar":"عَدِيتُ لَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I hated him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISd, K.)       -A4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EadaA","text_ar":"عَدَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also a verb by which one makes an exception, with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA","text_ar":"مَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[preceding it] and without"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA","text_ar":"مَا"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, K:) you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaA='aniY","text_ar":"جَا=ءَنِى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alqawomu maA EadaA zayodFA","text_ar":"القَوْمُ مَا عَدَا زَيْدًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The people,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"party, came to me, except Zeyd"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaAw^uwniY EadaA zayodFA","text_ar":"جَاوُونِى عَدَا زَيْدًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[which means the like]; putting what follows it in the accus. case; the agent being implied in it: (S: [see this expl. in what has been said of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xalaA","text_ar":"خَلَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"as used in the same manner:]) accord. to MF, it is a verb when what follows it is put in the accus. case; and when what follows it is put in the gen. case, it is a particle, by common consent: (TA: [and the like is said in the Mughnee; i. e., that it is similar to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xalaA","text_ar":"خَلَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"in respect of the explanations there given of the different usages of this latter; but that Sb did not know it to have been used otherwise than as having the quality of a verb:]) one says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA^ayotuhumo EadaA A^axaAka","text_ar":"رَاَيْتُهُمْ عَدَا اَخَاكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA EadaAhu","text_ar":"مَا عَدَاهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA xalaA","text_ar":"مَا خَلَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I saw them, except thy brother"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and sometimes it governs the gen. case without"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mA","text_ar":"ما"},{"kind":"text","text":": thus in the M: Az says, [as though regarding it as only a particle,] when you suppress ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mA","text_ar":"ما"},{"kind":"text","text":"], you make it to govern the accus. case as meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_il~aA","text_ar":"اـِلَّا"},{"kind":"text","text":"and you make it to govern the gen. case as meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"siwaY","text_ar":"سِوَى"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA."}],"source_refs":["Mgh","K","Msb","TA","S","ISd"]},{"entry_id":"n28370","headword_ar":"عداهٌ","root":"Edw","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taEodiyapN","text_ar":"تَعْدِيَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made him,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it, to pass"},{"kind":"text","text":"[from a thing, or an affair, to another: see 1, first sentence]: (S, K:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he made it to pass through, and go beyond;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^anofa*ahu","text_ar":"اَنْفَذَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) ―         -b2-  Hence"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taEodiyapu AlfiEoli","text_ar":"تَعْدِيَةُ الفِعْلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", a phrase of the grammarians, [generally meaning (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The making the verb transitive,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] as in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaraja zayodN faA^axorajotuhu","text_ar":"خَرَجَ زَيْدٌ فَاَخْرَجْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Zeyd went forth and I made him to go forth"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) ―         -b3-  See also 1, first quarter, in seven places: ―         -b4-  and again, in the latter half, in two places."}],"source_refs":["S","K"]}]}}